# Cursor IDE Rules and Conventions

## Conversation Tags

- <edited_file>: File being modified
- <current_file_contents>: Complete file content
- <edits_to_file>: Changes being made
- <assistant_edit>: AI suggested changes
- <human_edit>: User changes
- <user_action_hint>: User decisions/actions
- <relevant_files>: Related files for context
- <possibly_relevant_context>: Additional context
- <especially_relevant_code_snippet>: Important code sections

## Project-Specific Rules

1. File Organization
   - Follow structure in GUIDELINES.md
   - Keep imports organized per hierarchy
   - Use absolute imports across modules

2. Documentation Updates
   - Update relevant docs when changing structure
   - Keep dev_logs current
   - Follow documentation templates

3. Code Changes
   - Show file path with language ID
   - Use diff format for changes
   - Include context lines around changes

4. Testing
   - Update tests with code changes
   - Follow test naming conventions
   - Maintain test structure

